SENTENCE i was talking to one of my colleagues in the physics department the other day ,  and we ended up discussing how one discovery can change everything .
SENTENCE my colleague mentioned how the theory of relativity completely changed the field of physics .
SENTENCE at any rates ,  that conversation got me thinking about archaeological finds that really changed our understanding of ancient civilizations .
SENTENCE so i want to talk about the discovery of the antikythera mechanism .
SENTENCE the antikythera mechanism was found a hundred years ago ,  under water in an ancient greek shipwreck in the mediterranean sea .
SENTENCE it was in extremely poor condition and in many corroded pieces .
SENTENCE but once we figured out what it was and reconstructed it .
SENTENCE well ,  i simply don't have the words to convey how extraordinary this find was .
SENTENCE the antikythera mechanism is a relatively small device ,  roughly the size of a shoebox ,  made of gears fitted inside a wooden case .
SENTENCE in its original state ,  there were rotating dials and other indicators on the top ,  with letters and drawings showing the sun ,  the phases of the moon and different constellations .
SENTENCE inside the box ,  bronze gears would have rotated the displays .
SENTENCE the displays ,  uh ,  the indicators of the antikythera mechanism ,  would then moved to show the motion of the sun and moon relative to the planets and stars .
SENTENCE the device could be used to tell the different phases of the moon and much more .
SENTENCE well ,  scientists have recently analyzed the inscriptions on the mechanism and re examine the other cargo in the ship wreck ,  and the evidence makes an absolute case that this device dates back to ancient greece somewhere between 15  and 1   b .
